This paper is primarily focused on exploring the use of randomly wired neural networks for image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of neural architecture search (NAS), which is a topic within machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also touches on the idea of designing better network generators, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SI).
